# Playwright Testing Conventions

- Use stable selectors (`data-testid`) over brittle text-only locators when possible.
- Prefer deterministic seeded fixtures for assertions; avoid coupling tests to external AI/network behavior.
- Keep tests scenario-focused: one flow per test with clear arrange/act/assert structure.
- Assert visible user outcomes (counts, messages, rendered cards, dialog states), not internals.
- Capture and preserve failure diagnostics via traces/screenshots/videos.
- Avoid implicit sleeps; wait on explicit UI states or network/command completion signals.
